## đź”µ Find Command â€” Search Locations

| Symbol | Meaning | Searches From |
|---|---|---|
| `.` | Current directory | Where you are right now and all subdirectories below |
| `/` | Root directory | Entire system â€” every single file on the whole Linux system |
| `~` | Home directory | Your home folder and everything inside it |

**Example:**
```bash
find . -size 1033c    # search only current directory and below
find / -size 1033c    # search entire system from root
find ~ -size 1033c    # search only home directory and below
```

---

## đź”µ Find Command â€” Filter Parameters

| Filter | What it Does | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `-name "filename"` | Match exact filename | `find . -name "readme"` |
| `-name "*.txt"` | Match files by extension | `find . -name "*.txt"` |
| `-type f` | Files only (no folders) | `find . -type f` |
| `-type d` | Directories only (no files) | `find . -type d` |
| `-size 33c` | Exact size in bytes | `find . -size 33c` |
| `-size +1M` | Larger than 1 megabyte | `find . -size +1M` |
| `-size -1M` | Smaller than 1 megabyte | `find . -size -1M` |
| `-user username` | Owned by specific user | `find / -user bandit7` |
| `-group groupname` | Owned by specific group | `find / -group bandit6` |
| `-readable` | Human readable files only | `find . -readable` |
| `! -executable` | Files that are NOT executable | `find . ! -executable` |
| `-perm 777` | Files with exact permissions | `find . -perm 777` |

**Size Units:**
| Unit | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `c` | Bytes |
| `k` | Kilobytes |
| `M` | Megabytes |
| `G` | Gigabytes |

**Size Modifiers:**
| Modifier | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `33c` | Exactly 33 bytes |
| `+33c` | More than 33 bytes |
| `-33c` | Less than 33 bytes |

**Chaining Multiple Filters:**
```bash
# All filters are applied together â€” AND logic by default
find / -user bandit7 -group bandit6 -size 33c 2>/dev/null

# Use -o for OR logic between filters
find . -name "readme" -o -name "README"
```

